==English==

===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[έτυμον]]''' (''etymon'') "the true sense of a word according to its origin", from '''[[έτυμος]]''' (''etymos'') "true, real, actual".

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The source word of a given word. For example, the Latin '''[[candidus]]''' (white) is the etymon of the English '''[[candid]]'''.

